                        "content": "The nurse has been given a medication prescription to administer intravenous (IV) hydralazine. The nurse obtains which priority piece of equipment needed for use during administration of this medication?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale: \nHydralazine is an antihypertensive medication used for moderate to severe hypertension. Because the blood pressure and pulse need to be monitored frequently after administration, a noninvasive blood pressure cuff needs to be obtained. The other options are not priority items specific to the use of this medication.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nNote the strategic word, priority. Recalling that hydralazine is an antihypertensive will direct you to the correct option of a blood pressure cuff.\n\nClient Needs: Physiological Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Take Action\nCognitive Ability: Applying\nContent Area: Pharmacology: Cardiovascular: Antihypertensives\nHealth Problem: Adult Health: Cardiovascular: Hypertension\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Implementation\nPriority Concepts: Perfusion, Clinical Judgment\nStrategies: Strategic Words",
