                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale: \nWhen furosemide is administered by IV injection, each 40 mg or fraction thereof would be given over a 1- to 2-minute period. Options of 10 seconds and 30 seconds identify administration times that are too rapid and could cause adverse effects. Five minutes is too slow for administration and may affect the effectiveness of the IV medication.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, the time period for administering IV furosemide. Specific knowledge of this procedure is needed to answer correctly. First, eliminate options 1 and 2 as excessively brief. Regarding the remaining options, it is much more likely that the medication needs to be given over 2 minutes than 5 minutes.\n\nClient Needs: Physiological Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Take Action\nCognitive Ability: Applying\nContent Area: Adult Health: Cardiovascular\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Implementation\nPriority Concepts: Clinical Judgment, Safety\nStrategies: Subject",
